name: Cross of Mosses
description:
Grave found in the fishermen's cemetery on Honey Island.

Iha do Mel (Honey Island) is located in the South Atlantic Ocean and lies 15 miles from the Port of Paranaguá, with its closest point to the continent being 4 km from Pontal do Sul, in the municipality of Pontal do Paraná, on the coast of the state of Paraná, Brazil, known since the 17th century. In the 19th century it was used as a breeding island for slaves and also for the disposal of prisoners. Today it has an exclusively tourist function.

This tomb has no name, no date, nothing that can identify who lives here, just a cross full of moss and plants that grow from the tomb that was already left behind.
